</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">André Kostolany</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold"><span class="fn">André Kostolany</span></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Born</th>
<td><span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1906-02-09</span>)</span>9 February 1906<br />
<span class="birthplace"><a href="/wiki/Budapest" title="Budapest">Budapest</a>, <a href="/wiki/Austria-Hungary" title="Austria-Hungary">Austria-Hungary</a></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Died</th>
<td>14 September 1999<span style="display:none">(<span class="dday deathdate">1999-09-14</span>)</span> (aged&#160;93)<br />
<span class="deathplace"><a href="/wiki/Paris" title="Paris">Paris</a>, <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Nationality</th>
<td class="category"><a href="/wiki/Hungary" title="Hungary">Hungary</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Occupation</th>
<td class="role"><a href="/wiki/Speculator" title="Speculator" class="mw-redirect">Speculator</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>André Kostolany</b> (February 9, 1906 – September 14, 1999) was a <a href="/wiki/Stock_market" title="Stock market">stock market</a> expert, bon vivant and <a href="/wiki/Chevalier_de_la_L%C3%A9gion_d%27Honneur" title="Chevalier de la Légion d'Honneur" class="mw-redirect">Chevalier de la Légion d'Honneur</a>. He worked most of his life in <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a> and <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">Germany</a>.</p>
<p></p>
